I was able to resolve the issue.

We have a custom connector implemented for decrypting the keystore and key passwords from the application.properties file. This implementation is very similar to how it has been shown in this link: https://frugalisminds.com/how-to-configure-ssl-in-spring-boot-2/

However, trying to set the properties/attributes on the new custom connector was causing this issue:

    connector.setAttribute(&quot;keyAlias&quot;, &lt;alias&gt;);
    connector.setAttribute(&quot;keystorePass&quot;, &lt;password&gt;);
    connector.setAttribute(&quot;keystoreFile&quot;, &lt;file&gt;);

So, instead of adding custom connector and setting the values, I am modifying the default connector itself as below:

    public void customize(TomcatServletWebServerFactory factory) {
      if (Boolean.valueOf(sslEnabled)) {
        // Force the passwords in the default connector to be updated with decrypted passwords
        factory.getSsl().setKeyPassword(&lt;key-password&gt;);
        factory.getSsl().setKeyStorePassword(&lt;keystore-password&gt;);
      }
    }

Hope this help, thanks!

